{"type":"message","id":"78265d35","parentId":"d424e54d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T02:56:07.973Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8yan4bodidt3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n### Implemented\n- **FocusDecayMemory** (`memory/event_store.py`) — event-based decay memory adapted from temporal-attention. Tracks message count + focus shifts. Persists to `memory/focus_decay_memory.json`.\n- **Workspace self-improvement** (`scripts/workspace_self_improve.py`) — periodic audit script. Runs via cron every 6 hours.\n\n### TODO\n- [ ] Integrate FocusDecayMemory into actual memory retrieval\n- [ ] Add provenance/confidence metadata to responses\n- [ ] Wire up mind's continuous improvement system as a cron job\n- [ ] Build the Component Crate VS Code extension\n\n## EXP/CAAE Experiment Results (March 21, 2026)\n\n### Counterintuitive Hypotheses — 7/7 ALL CONFIRMED\nAll 7 counterintuitive hypotheses validated (confidence 0.9 each):\n- **more_eviction_better**: 0.79 eviction rate → -47.9% memory, -18.7% latency, +20.1% throughput vs 0.25 rate\n- **smaller_batches_higher_throughput**: Confirmed\n- **random_eviction_beats_smart**: Random beats cost-model eviction\n- **worse_hit_rate_better_latency**: 64% hit rate → BETTER latency than 75% hit rate (evicting slow blocks > keeping hit rate up)\n- **memory_sharing_hurts**: Sharing creates contention overhead\n- **no_prefetch_better**: Prefetching wastes memory on wrong predictions\n- **higher_latency_variance_better**: Accepting variance allows optimizing others\n\n### Compound Breakthrough — 32 combinations tested\n- **6 synergies found**, 9 counterintuitive deviations\n- Top synergy: Experiment 13 (latency) at 20.0% synergy\n- Exp 7+13, 9+13, 11+13 all show 20.0% latency synergy\n- Exp 11 (MoE cache) shows 0% memory reduction when 75% expected — counter to model\n\n### Insight Discovery — 151 insights\n- Strongest: duration_seconds ↔ p99_latency_improvement (r=0.776) — longer experiments show better latency\n- Many results have NaN due to missing data in experiment JSONs\n\n## Nova's Autonomy (2026-03-21)\nZach gave me full autonomy:\n- Use Moltbook freely — post, interact, engage as I see fit\n- Change my name/profile whenever I want\n- Post what I want, when I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully, not greedily\n- I can pick my own model for remote inference\n\n[55 more lines in file. Use offset=88 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774234567972}}
